{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getSystemConfigDirs","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">?>!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On UNIX platforms this is determined using the mechanisms described","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"http:\/\/www.freedesktop.org\/Standards\/basedir-spec","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In this case the list of directories retrieved will be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"XDG_CONFIG_DIRS"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows it follows XDG Base Directory Specification if "},{"code":"XDG_CONFIG_DIRS","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is defined."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"XDG_CONFIG_DIRS"},{"text":" is undefined, the directory that contains application","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"data for all users is used instead. A typical path is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"C:\\Documents and Settings\\All Users\\Application Data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This folder is used for application data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that is not user specific. For example, an application can store","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a spell-check dictionary, a database of clip art, or a log file in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"FOLDERID_ProgramData folder. This information will not roam and is available"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to anyone using the computer.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The return value is cached and modifying it at runtime is not supported, as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it’s not thread-safe to modify environment variables at runtime."}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/getSystemConfigDirs()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Function","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getSystemConfigDirs","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">?>!"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"func","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"getSystemConfigDirs()","externalID":"s:4GLib19getSystemConfigDirsSPySPys4Int8VGSgGSgyF"},"abstract":[{"text":"Returns an ordered list of base directories in which to access","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"system-wide configuration information.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/getsystemconfigdirs()"]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role